From: Jayanth Othayoth <ojayanth@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 6 Dec 2024 09:13:18 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] clang-tidy: Initial commit

Added initial .clang-tidy configuration file with recommended C++ checks
aligned with the OpenBMC-approved checklist. This setup enforces modern
C++ best practices and helps catch common issues early in development.

Change-Id: I0adf1e0678210f775a20b229f639c9dd49dd9c8e
Signed-off-by: Jayanth Othayoth <ojayanth@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Akash A <mirrorghost007@gmail.com>
---
 .clang-tidy | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 .clang-tidy

diff --git a/.clang-tidy b/.clang-tidy
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..7c0c50d0
--- /dev/null
+++ b/.clang-tidy
@@ -0,0 +1,10 @@
+Checks: '-*,
+    bugprone-unchecked-optional-access,
+    modernize-use-nullptr
+    '
+
+CheckOptions: []
+
+HeaderFilterRegex: (?!^subprojects).*
+
+WarningsAsErrors: '*'
-- 
